Description: Clay sealing; on front, partial impression of seal with hieroglyphic inscription, title of prophet followed by names; back with impression of strings.
Curator's comments: The title of prophet (Hm-nTr) was high in the sacerdotal hierarchy in Ancient Egypt (de Meulenaere 1982; Gee 2004). For seal impressions bearing sacerdotal title(s) followed by name(s) and dating to the Late Period, see for example: Bietak and Reiser-Haslauer 1982, p. 189-190, n°559; Masson 2007, 615-616; Masson 2010; Masson forthcoming.
